98.1	Druze	Druze	The Druze are a monotheistic religious community, found primarily in Syria, Lebanon, Israel, and Jordan, which emerged during the 11th century from Ismailism. Druze beliefs incorporate several elements from Abrahamic religions, Gnosticism, Neoplatonism and other philosophies. The Druze call themselves Ahl al-Tawhid the People of Monotheism or al-Muwaḥḥidūn "the Unitarians".	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/36/Druze_star.svg/100px-Druze_star.svg.png
